## 3. Head-to-Head Comparison

| Criterion | info1 (NEXUS) | info2 (ENTERPRISE) | Verdict |
|-----------|---------------|--------------------|---------| 
| **Guidewire Alignment** | ❌ Zero integration | ✅ APD, PolicyCenter, ClaimCenter, Integration Gateway | **info2 wins decisively** |
| **Innovation Score** | 2/5 — standard weather API + ML | 4.5/5 — Shield-SAC + PADS + Guidewire-native | **info2** |
| **Feasibility** | 4/5 — simple stack, proven tech | 3/5 — too many bleeding-edge components | **info1** |
| **Technical Depth** | 2.5/5 — Scikit-learn + anomaly detection | 4.5/5 — DRL, physics fraud, XAI | **info2** |
| **Demo Readiness** | 4/5 — clear 5-min flow | 4.5/5 — emotional + technical script | **info2** |
| **Impact Narrative** | 3/5 — "income protection" | 4.5/5 — "enterprise transformation for India" | **info2** |
| **Fraud Sophistication** | 2/5 — device + GPS + basic anomaly | 4/5 — PADS kinematics + future GNN | **info2** |
| **Risk Management** | Low risk, low reward | High risk, high reward (with identified mitigations) | **Depends on execution** |

### Gap Analysis — What NEITHER File Addresses

| Missing Element | Importance | Our Fix |
|-----------------|------------|---------|
| **Guidewire Marketplace alignment** | Critical — judges want solutions they can productize | Position as a Marketplace-ready InsurTech module |
| **WhatsApp/voice onboarding** | High — 80% of gig workers use WhatsApp, not apps | Add WhatsApp Bot + IVR for regional language onboarding |
| **Peer/community insurance** | Medium — mutual aid groups are culturally resonant | "Shield Pools": Workers in same zone share risk |
| **Earned wage access integration** | Medium — connects insurance to existing fintech rails | Partner narrative with EWA platforms (Refyne, EarlySalary) |
| **Government scheme mapping** | High — IRDAI/PMJJBY alignment shows policy awareness | Map product to existing government programs |
| **Sustainability model** | Critical — judges want to see how this survives post-hackathon | Show unit economics: loss ratio, expected claims ratio, CAC |

